sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as External Client
    participant Router as OpenShift Router<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.3
    participant RBACProxy as kube-rbac-proxy<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS
    participant RestAPI as Model Registry REST<br/>8080/TCP HTTP
    participant DB as PostgreSQL<br/>5432/TCP (Optional TLS)

    Note over Client,DB: Flow 1: External User Access to Model Registry (Secured)

    Client->>Router: POST /api/model_registry/v1alpha3/models<br/>Auth: Bearer Token
    Router->>RBACProxy: Forward (TLS reencrypt)<br/>443 → 8443
    RBACProxy->>K8sAPI: SubjectAccessReview<br/>Validate Bearer Token
    K8sAPI-->>RBACProxy: Authorized: true
    RBACProxy->>RestAPI: Forward request (localhost)<br/>8080/TCP HTTP
    RestAPI->>DB: SELECT model metadata<br/>Auth: Password/Client Cert
    DB-->>RestAPI: Model records
    RestAPI-->>RBACProxy: JSON Response
    RBACProxy-->>Router: HTTPS Response
    Router-->>Client: Model metadata

    Note over Client,DB: Flow 2: Operator Reconciliation

    participant Controller as Controller Manager
    participant Webhook as Webhook Service<br/>9443/TCP HTTPS

    Controller->>K8sAPI: Watch ModelRegistry CRs<br/>ServiceAccount token
    K8sAPI->>Webhook: ValidatingWebhook<br/>POST /validate-*<br/>mTLS
    Webhook-->>K8sAPI: Validation result
    K8sAPI-->>Controller: CR event (create/update)
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create Deployment<br/>Create Service<br/>Create Route
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create NetworkPolicy<br/>Isolate database access

    Note over Client,DB: Flow 3: Internal Model Registry Access (No Proxy)

    participant InternalPod as Internal Pod
    participant Service as {registry-name} Service<br/>8080/TCP HTTP

    InternalPod->>Service: GET /api/model_registry/v1alpha3/models<br/>No Auth
    Service->>RestAPI: Forward (ClusterIP)
    RestAPI->>DB: Query metadata<br/>Auth: Password
    DB-->>RestAPI: Results
    RestAPI-->>Service: JSON Response
    Service-->>InternalPod: Model data

    Note over Client,DB: Flow 4: Database Initialization (Auto-Provisioned)

    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create PVC<br/>Create PostgreSQL Deployment<br/>Create Database Service
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create Database Secret<br/>(credentials)
    RestAPI->>DB: Connect with credentials<br/>Run schema migrations
    DB-->>RestAPI: Schema created
